# Submission by Rajagopal (Raj) Ramanujam
# Thera Bank Personal Loan Campaign
Dataset: * ID: Customer ID * Age: Customer's age in completed years * Experience: #years of professional experience * Income: Annual income of the customer ($000) * ZIP Code: Home Address ZIP code. * Family: Family size of the customer * CCAvg: Avg. spending on credit cards per month ($000) * Education: Education Level. 1: Undergrad; 2: Graduate; 3: Advanced/Professional * Mortgage: Value of house mortgage if any. ($000) * Personal Loan: Did this customer accept the personal loan offered in the last campaign? * Securities Account: Does the customer have a securities account with the bank? * CD Account: Does the customer have a certificate of deposit (CD) account with the bank? * Online: Does the customer use internet banking facilities? * Credit card: Does the customer use a credit card issued by the bank?

Inference¶

If skewness value is zero than it is not skewed If it is less than zero then negatively skewed (left tail) and if greater than zero then positively skewed (right tail)

**Data for most of the attributes (Age, Experience, Income, Family, CCAvg, Education, Mortgage, Personal Loan, Securities Account, CD Account, Online and Credit Card) seems to be skewed.

**Particularly CD Account, Securities Account, Personal Loan, Mortgage and CCAvg are highly skewed (right tail).

**Additionally Experience column contains negative values which can't be true and needs to be fixed

## function to get confusion matrix in a proper format
def draw_cm( actual, predicted ):
    cm = confusion_matrix( actual, predicted)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True,  fmt='.2f', xticklabels = [0,1] , yticklabels = [0,1] )
    plt.ylabel('Observed')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted')
    plt.show()

Question#6 - Give Business understanding of your model? (5 marks)¶

# Confusion matrix means True Positive (observed=1,predicted=1): Predicted that customer will apply for loan and the customer applied False Positive (observed=0,predicted=1): Predicted that customer will apply for loan and the customer didn't apply True Negative (observed=0,predicted=0): Predicted that customer will not apply for loan and the customer didn't apply for loan False Negative (observed=1,predicted=0): Predicted that customer will not apply for loan and the customer applied Here the bank wants to give personal loans to the people who are eligible i.e. more TP and less FN so that the bank doesn't lose customers. Hence Recall or Sensitivity is the important metric. In case of False positive bank i.e., predicted that customer will apply for loan and the customer didn't apply can be higher since the bussiness goal is to convert more liability customers into personal loan customers. After achieving the desired accuracy we can deploy the model for practical use. As in the bank now can predict who is eligible for home loan. They can use the model for upcoming customers.
In [ ]:
